entries.title: Retailers fear London will be a 'sideshow' for tourists without the return of VAT-free shopping
entries.description: Shaftesbury boss Brian Bickell (pictured) said luxury retailers are diverting money away from the capital and investing more in European rivals Paris, Milan and Rome.

entries.title: Princess of Wales kicks off Place2Be's Children's Mental Health Week
entries.description: Kate Middleton, 41, discussed the importance of opening up about how you feel as she sat and coloured with the kids at St John's CE Primary School in Bethnal Green.

entries.title: Nursing union chiefs hint they might accept HALF their previous pay demands
entries.description: 40,000 nurses and ambulance staff are striking today in the biggest day of industrial action to hit the NHS. Ministers warned yesterday that lives will be put at risk by the walkout.

entries.title: Sydney school Queenwood bans AFL over concerns of brain injuries
entries.description: Students at Queenwood, on Sydney's north shore, have been banned from playing AFL after the school hierarchy heard teenage girls are the most likely to develop traumatic brain injuries.

entries.title: Australian worker shortage: Businesses offer odd perks to bring employees in
entries.description: Australian businesses have started offering employees insane perks - like skydiving session and a lifetime supply of chocolate - to hold onto dwindling employees and lure in new ones.

entries.title: Meghan Markle 'will not like' Sasha Walpole revealing how she took Prince Harry's virginity
entries.description: The Duchess of Sussex will be displeased by Prince Harry's 'older woman' speaking out, a royal commentator claimed. Sasha Walpole, 40, revealed that she was the first lover of the Prince.
